y TenThousand Projects and [[Caroline Records]] on the duo's second album ''Where the Light Is'' on January 8, 2019. The song's music video was released on July 11, 2019 and it shows the duo turning a boring office to a party place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Surfaces-Shares-New-Music-Video-For-SUNDAY-BEST-20190711|title=Surfaces Shares New Music Video For SUNDAY BEST|date=July 11, 2019|website=[[BroadwayWorld]]|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song is believed to have gained popularity in late February 2020 on the online-video sharing platform [[TikTok]] for it's lyric \"Feeling good, like I should\",<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/business/branding/8551350/flighthouse-republic-records-partner-tiktok-series-certified-superfan|title=Flighthouse and Republic Records Partner on New TikTok Series 'Certified Superfan'|last=Eggertsen|first=Chris|date=February 19, 2020|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|url-status=live|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> before it was released for radio airplay in early March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|title=Top 40/M Future Releases|date=March 3, 2020|website=[[All Access]]|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302133607/https://www.allaccess.com/top40-mainstream/future-releases|archive-date=March 2, 2020|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.top-charts.com/s/sunday-best-surfaces|title=Sunday Best by Surfaces|website=Top-Charts.com|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref> The song peaked in the Top 40 in Australia, Canada, Norway, Ireland, New Zealand and the United Kingdom, as well as the top 100 in the United States, Switzerland, Germany and Sweden. \n\n== Live performances ==\nSurfaces made their late-night television debut when they performed the song on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' on March 2, 2020.<ref>{{Cite w